The original Stage-Gate system was created in the 1980s,  based on an in-depth study of successful “intrapreneurs”  within major corporations as they drove successful new  products to market. Their practices and the lessons they  learned provided the foundation for that early stage-and- gate model. Over the years, Stage-Gate has evolved and in- corporated many new practices (see, for instance, Cooper  1994 , 2008 , 2011 ). Some companies have also developed  their own versions of Stage-Gate, building in some positive  elements, but also some negative ones.
